description:
&lt;h1&gt;Pre-Operative Assessment Nurse&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Queen Alexandra Hospital has a reputation as a dynamic and innovative place to work. Its Theatres are leading the way in Robotic Surgery and it is recognised as a Worldwide Centre of Excellence.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There are 27 modern, state-of- the- art theatres across 2 floors which undertake elective, emergency and trauma work for both Adults and Paediatrics. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Whether you are a newly qualified Staff Nurse or RODP with experience, we have an opportunity for you within our Pre-Operative Assessment Clinic.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-assessment personnel play a pivotal role in delivering safe and efficient pre-operative care by optimising patients for surgery. You will be working with the multi-disciplinary teams, including GP’s and Anaesthetists to provide effective assessment to ensure that our patients and their families/carers receive excellent preparation for surgical procedures.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our pre-assessment service covers a number of specialties and you will play an important role in assessing patients for a variety of procedures including ENT, Orthopaedics, Urology, Gynae, Breast and General Surgery.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a motivated and dynamic individual who can demonstrate the distinctive professional and personal skills required to work within the Pre-operative Assessment Team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A positive attitude, outstanding communication ability, exceptional interpersonal skills, initiative and dynamism are imperative. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous experience of working within a pre-operative assessment role would be desirable. However, the successful candidates will be provided with a comprehensive training package upon appointment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;What you can expect from us&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have a number of dedicated Educational/Training mornings identified throughout the year and an excellent IT facility to support with on-line training. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be supported by an enthusiastic team in order to help you develop pre-operative assessment skills across a number of specialtes. A competency based training package and working alongside experienced personnel will be provided in order to achieve this.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rotational posts with other departments within the Care Group are actively encouraged and full support will be given to develop the successful candidates to their full potential:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Staff benefits include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TOPS Day Nursery + childcare vouchers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oasis well-being and Fitness Centre&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Handbook&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acquillis Counselling Service &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;and many more…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;We are looking for:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Band 5 RN or RODP with a surgical background or experience of pre-operative assessment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be expected to work with a variety of specialties and liaise with other members of the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be open and adaptable to learning new skills and developing your skills further.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should be either a Registered Nurse or Operating Department Practitioner who is flexible in your working approach with the ability to demonstrate forward thinking and problem solving.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are interested in joining our multi-cultural cohesive team, please call Jo Hall on 02392 28600 ext 4086 for an informal chat or visit. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
